Fk9 Mark 1 is a variant of B&F Fk9.
Fk9 Mark 1 has composite wings.
Fk9 Mark 1 has metal tube fuselage.
Fk9 Mark 1 was the first production version.
Fk9 Mark 1 was introduced in 1991.
Fk9 Mark 2 is a variant of B&F Fk9.
Fk9 Mark 2 was revised to accept more powerful engines.
Fk9 Mark 2 accepts engines between 45-80 horsepower.
Fk9 Mark 2 has conventional gear.
Fk9 Mark 2 was introduced in 1995.
Fk9TG is a variant of B&F Fk9.
Fk9TG is a Mark 2 with tricycle gear.
Fk9 Mark 3 is a variant of B&F Fk9.
Fk9 Mark 3 is the first all-composites version.
Fk9 Mark 3 has a strongly revised fuselage shape.
Fk9 Mark 3 has a more slender aft.
Fk9 Mark 3 was introduced in 1997.
Mark 38 is a variant of B&F Fk9.
Mark 38 is marketed in Brazil as Alpha Bravo Fk9.
Mark 38 has a wingspan of 10.33 meters.
Mark 3 Utility/Club is a variant of B&F Fk9.
Mark 3 Utility/Club is designed for trainer or glider towing roles.
Mark 3 Utility/Club has new wings.
Mark 3 Utility/Club was introduced in 2000.
Fk9 Smart is a variant of B&F Fk9.
Fk9 Smart is powered by Ecofly M160 three-cylinder turbocharged diesel engine.
Ecofly M160 engine is from Smart car.
Ecofly M160 engine produces 100 horsepower (75 kilowatts) at 5600 rpm.
Fk9 Smart was introduced in 2004.

text:
## Variants
Information from

Fk9 Mark 1
Composite wings, metal tube fuselage.  First production version. Introduced 1991.
Fk9 Mark 2
Revised to accept more powerful (4580 hp) engines. Conventional gear.  Introduced 1995.
Fk9TG: Mark 2 with tricycle gear.

Fk9 Mark 3
First all-composites version; fuselage shape strongly revised, more slender aft. Introduced 1997.
Mark 38: Marketed in Brazil as Alpha Bravo Fk9.  Span 10.33 m.
Mark 3 Utility/Club: For trainer or glider towing roles. New wings. Introduced 2000.
Fk9 Smart
powered by Ecofly M160 three-cylinder turbocharged diesel engine from Smart car, producing 100 hp (75 kW) at 5600 rpm.  Introduced 2004.
